After the offer to his slave for ever he let me loot the heart (he was like...what the heck it for?)

Time camped of live grimrot = 0.

Later that day I came back to the camp and thought...well might as well see if he spawns. Maybe 90 mins later (got bored as I don't know don't normally camp that long for something where there is no exp) the live grimrot spawned.  I have a look in the zone and ask a level 40 monk if he could spare a bit of time he said sure and dragged another monk and a shaman to kill the live version (they were shocked how hard he was).

Needless to say we killed it and they made a friend for life (Holy monks of the tribunal I salute you).

Now the faction...that was another story altogether (only I could get run over by a hill giant whilst meditating in west karana heh).  Spent 2 weeks on bandits before giving up and doing the fishy quest.

Regarding the camp though...I always been lucky at camping things that I aint camping...its when I try to camp things (did 5 consecutive regis spawns once only to lose them all :<) that they become difficult.

Aldur - 46th Cleric of the Tribunal (born lucky only ever rolled for 2 ssoy ....won 2.  Rolled 100 both times)
